        }
      ],
      "content": "The `useNodeActions()` hook from `@powerhousedao/reactor-browser` returns an object with drive file/folder operations: `onAddFile(file: File, parent: Node | undefined)` adds a file under a parent folder; `onAddFolder(name, parent)` creates a folder; `onRenameNode(newName, node)` renames; `onCopyNode(src, target)` copies to a target folder; `onMoveNode(src, target)` moves; `onDuplicateNode(src)` duplicates in the current folder; `onAddAndSelectNewFolder(name)` creates and selects a new folder. All return Promises. The drive structure uses `Node` (FileNode | FolderNode) hierarchy, queryable via `useNodesInSelectedDrive`, `useFileNodesInSelectedDrive`, `useFolderNodesInSelectedDrive`, and their folder-scoped variants.",
